========================================
Audit Policy Configuration
========================================

[Overview]
The following audit policies were configured to support security monitoring
and detection of suspicious activity within the Active Directory environment.

[Configured Policies]
- Logon/Logoff Auditing        : Success, Failure
- Account Lockout Monitoring   : Enabled
- Credential Validation        : Enabled
- Object Access Auditing       : Enabled

[Purpose]
These settings allow for visibility into authentication activity, account
lockouts, and file access events, which are critical for detecting
unauthorized behavior.

[Relevant Event IDs]
- 4624 : Successful Logon
- 4625 : Failed Logon Attempt
- 4740 : Account Lockout
- 4663 : File Access Activity
